@ijuma There's actually only two usages of the precedes() function currently. The first is used in `Partition` to determine if the high watermark should be updated. Checking the segment base offset makes sense to me in this case since we should update the high watermark when the segment changes. 

The other case is in `DelayedFetch` and the segment base offset check doesn't make as much sense since there is already an explicit prior check to handle differing segment offsets.

So maybe we could revert the precedes() change and just modify the check in `maybeIncrementLeaderHW` to check the segment base offset explicitly (e.g. with `LogOffsetMetadata.offsetOnOlderSegment`). What do you think?

@ijuma I will start a poll on the mailing list as Jun suggested.

